27 SECTION 5. ORS 430.383 is amended to read:
28 430.383. (1)(a) The people of Oregon find that drug addiction and overdoses are a serious prob-
29 lem in Oregon and that Oregon needs to expand access to drug treatment.
30 (b) The people of Oregon further find that a health-based approach to addiction and overdose is
31 [more] effective, humane and cost-effective [than criminal punishments. Making people criminals be-
32 cause they suffer from addiction is expensive, ruins lives and can make access to treatment and recov-
33 ery more difficult].
34 (2)(a) The purpose of the Drug Addiction Treatment and Recovery Act of 2020, as amended, is
35 to make screening, health assessment, treatment and recovery services for drug addiction available
36 to all those who need and want access to those services and to [adopt a health approach] enhance
37 assessment, treatment and recovery services to address drug addiction [by removing criminal
38 penalties for low-level drug possession].
39 (b) It is the policy of the State of Oregon:
40 (A) That screening, health assessment, treatment and recovery services for drug addiction are
41 available to all those who need and want access to those services; and
42 (B) To encourage treatment and recovery for people struggling with substance use.
43 (3) The provisions of ORS 430.383 to 430.390 and 430.394 shall be interpreted consistently with
44 the findings, purposes and policy objectives stated in this section and shall not be limited by any
45 policy set forth in Oregon law that could conflict with or be interpreted to conflict with the pur-
